{"data":{"featured":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Radioactive Waste Disposal","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/mobile/static/b38723c0a9e682b8f64b5eb51f359255/d2194/paper-cover.png","srcSet":"/mobile/static/b38723c0a9e682b8f64b5eb51f359255/cebcc/paper-cover.png 175w,\n/mobile/static/b38723c0a9e682b8f64b5eb51f359255/272cf/paper-cover.png 350w,\n/mobile/static/b38723c0a9e682b8f64b5eb51f359255/d2194/paper-cover.png 700w","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/b38723c0a9e682b8f64b5eb51f359255/9aa63/paper-cover.avif 175w,\n/mobile/static/b38723c0a9e682b8f64b5eb51f359255/e6db6/paper-cover.avif 350w,\n/mobile/static/b38723c0a9e682b8f64b5eb51f359255/f47db/paper-cover.avif 700w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/b38723c0a9e682b8f64b5eb51f359255/240e7/paper-cover.webp 175w,\n/mobile/static/b38723c0a9e682b8f64b5eb51f359255/faefe/paper-cover.webp 350w,\n/mobile/static/b38723c0a9e682b8f64b5eb51f359255/d5dc4/paper-cover.webp 700w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"}]},"width":700,"height":438}}},"tech":["Hohmann Transfer","Collision Probability"],"github":null,"external":"https://doi.org/10.13140/RG.2.2.32859.41761","cta":"http://www.uphysicsc.com/2016contest.html","subtitle":"Silver Medal Winner @The 2016 University Physics Competition"},"html":"<p>In this investigation of whether the process of disposal of throwing into Sun or the process of storing waste in asteroid belt is easier. We calculated the amount of thrust required for a space probe carrying nuclear waste. The delta-v required for direct solar impact and solar impact via Jupiter swing-by is 29.8 km/s and 7.174 km/s respectively. Again the thrust required for the probe to reach asteroid belt is 6.274 km/s. From the calculation of probability of collision we got the frequency of collision is 3.49 x 10^(17) year km^(-2). Comparing these results we concluded that storing nuclear waste in asteroid belt is more safe and easier.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Electromagnetic Two Body Problem","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/mobile/static/bc90d5dd6eb2bdc3b8faea8ffb2a7b1e/d2194/cover.png","srcSet":"/mobile/static/bc90d5dd6eb2bdc3b8faea8ffb2a7b1e/cebcc/cover.png 175w,\n/mobile/static/bc90d5dd6eb2bdc3b8faea8ffb2a7b1e/272cf/cover.png 350w,\n/mobile/static/bc90d5dd6eb2bdc3b8faea8ffb2a7b1e/d2194/cover.png 700w","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/bc90d5dd6eb2bdc3b8faea8ffb2a7b1e/9aa63/cover.avif 175w,\n/mobile/static/bc90d5dd6eb2bdc3b8faea8ffb2a7b1e/e6db6/cover.avif 350w,\n/mobile/static/bc90d5dd6eb2bdc3b8faea8ffb2a7b1e/f47db/cover.avif 700w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/bc90d5dd6eb2bdc3b8faea8ffb2a7b1e/240e7/cover.webp 175w,\n/mobile/static/bc90d5dd6eb2bdc3b8faea8ffb2a7b1e/faefe/cover.webp 350w,\n/mobile/static/bc90d5dd6eb2bdc3b8faea8ffb2a7b1e/d5dc4/cover.webp 700w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"}]},"width":700,"height":438}}},"tech":["Lienard-Wiechert Potential","Lorentz Force"],"github":null,"external":"https://doi.org/10.13140/RG.2.2.13267.22562","cta":null,"subtitle":"National Conference on Physics - 2019, University of Dhaka"},"html":"<p>A system of two classical point charges governed by the Maxwell's Theory of Electrodynamics and the Lorentz force is considered with relativistic rigor. The solution of the equation of motion for those charged particles are obtained numerically by using the Runge-Kutta Method. The results show a variance with the usual concept of classical electrodynamics. The reason of the abnormalities and the necessary consideration for the allowable solution of the system are reviewed for further analysis.</p>"}}]}}}